text: The Chandler House, at 167 S. Main St. in Walton, Kentucky, was built in the 1920s. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1989. The listing included two contributing buildings. It was deemed significant "as a good example of the Craftsman/Bungalow style, significant to Boone County in the period 1905-1930."
